# Mobile Accessibility Checklist

## Mobile-Specific Accessibility Requirements

### Touch Target Size
- [ ] Minimum touch target size of 44x44 pixels (iOS) or 48x48dp (Android)
- [ ] Adequate spacing between touch targets (minimum 8px)
- [ ] Touch targets do not overlap

### Mobile Screen Reader Testing
- [ ] Test with VoiceOver (iOS) and TalkBack (Android)
- [ ] Swipe navigation works correctly
- [ ] Touch exploration provides meaningful feedback

### Mobile Keyboard Support
- [ ] External keyboard navigation works on tablets
- [ ] On-screen keyboard doesn't obscure content
- [ ] Focus moves logically with keyboard input

### Orientation and Zoom
- [ ] Content reflows properly in portrait and landscape
- [ ] Zoom up to 200% works without horizontal scrolling
- [ ] Content remains functional when zoomed

### Mobile Form Accessibility
- [ ] Input types are appropriate (email, tel, number, etc.)
- [ ] Autocomplete attributes are used where applicable
- [ ] Error messages are clearly associated with form fields

### Gesture Accessibility
- [ ] Complex gestures have simple alternatives
- [ ] Drag and drop operations have keyboard alternatives
- [ ] Swipe actions are announced to screen readers

## Testing Tools for Mobile
- **iOS**: VoiceOver, Accessibility Inspector
- **Android**: TalkBack, Accessibility Scanner
- **Cross-platform**: axe DevTools mobile testing
